In October 2015, my friend [Dan Gries](https://dangries.com) and I got to decorate the windows of the New Haven Armory on Goffe Street, for [City Wide Open Studios](htttps://www.cwos.org). They were covered in metal grids, and, like we had with [the Marilyn Monroe piece](/projects/pool-noodle-marilyn) we did for Re:Generate 2014, we stuffed the grid with chunks of pool noodles.

