We had sixteen grids that were about 30" wide, 72" tall. That meant buying a lot of pool noodles.

## Preparing the pool noodles

While Dan did a lot of the image and software work, I cut up over 250 pool
noodles with a bandsaw. First, in half lengthwise, then each half into
quarters, then each quarter into slices. The final images were composed of
25,352 pieces, and we finished with some leftover stock.

